<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFEAFFB0FF36771ED9E8FDCC" blockId="91.[189,562,531,591]" box="[189,400,569,591]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">
(
<figureCitation id="66FDD1A5FFEAFFB0FF4A771ED940FDCC" box="[193,312,569,591]" captionStart="Figs 160–180" captionStartId="17.[151,191,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1397,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-153@17.[151,1398,232,1964]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 160–180. Tetrabothrus borneensis, holotype (160–162), T. punctiventris (163–166), T. sulawesicus (167–169), Zyras illecebrosus, paratype (170–172), Z. gibbus, holotype (173–177), and Z. quasar, holotype (178–180): forebody (160, 163, 167, 170, 173, 178); antenna (161, 164, 168, 171, 174, 179); abdomen (162, 165, 169, 172, 175, 180); tergite VIII (166); tergite III (176); tergites VII– VIII (177). Scale bars: 160–165, 167–175, 178–180: 1.0 mm; 166, 176–177: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421194/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">Figs 170–172</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="66FDD1A5FFEAFFB0FEB4771ED9F4FDCC" box="[319,396,569,591]" captionStart="Figs 442–458" captionStartId="31.[151,191,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[155,1398,240,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-119@31.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 442–458. Tetrabothrus collucatus (442–443), T. borneensis (444–449), T. punctiventris (450–451), T. sulawesicus (452–454), Zyras illecebrosus, paratype (455–456), and Z. quasar, holotype (457–458): median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (442–445, 450–453, 455–458); apico-ventral portion of median lobe in lateral view (446–448); male sternite VIII (449, 454). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421226/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">455–456</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFEAFFB0FF1C774DDA66FD42" blockId="91.[150,756,617,705]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">
Two 
<typeStatus id="217D7382FFEAFFB0FF40774DD949FD01" box="[203,305,618,642]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">paratypes</typeStatus>
were examined earlier (
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFEAFFB0FDA5774EDAC2FD02" author="ASSING, V." box="[558,698,617,641]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104" pagination="87 - 175" refId="ref76876" refString="ASSING, V. 2016: A revision of Zyras STEPHENS sensu strictu of China, Taiwan, and Hong Kong, with records and (re-) descriptions of some species from other regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Lomechusini). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 9: 87 - 175." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The external and male sexual characters of one of them are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="66FDD1A5FFEAFFB0FEAF778ED9CAFD42" box="[292,434,681,705]" captionStart="Figs 160–180" captionStartId="17.[151,191,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1397,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-153@17.[151,1398,232,1964]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 160–180. Tetrabothrus borneensis, holotype (160–162), T. punctiventris (163–166), T. sulawesicus (167–169), Zyras illecebrosus, paratype (170–172), Z. gibbus, holotype (173–177), and Z. quasar, holotype (178–180): forebody (160, 163, 167, 170, 173, 178); antenna (161, 164, 168, 171, 174, 179); abdomen (162, 165, 169, 172, 175, 180); tergite VIII (166); tergite III (176); tergites VII– VIII (177). Scale bars: 160–165, 167–175, 178–180: 1.0 mm; 166, 176–177: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421194/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">Figs 170–172</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="66FDD1A5FFEAFFB0FE36778EDA62FD42" box="[445,538,681,705]" captionStart="Figs 442–458" captionStartId="31.[151,191,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[155,1398,240,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-119@31.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 442–458. Tetrabothrus collucatus (442–443), T. borneensis (444–449), T. punctiventris (450–451), T. sulawesicus (452–454), Zyras illecebrosus, paratype (455–456), and Z. quasar, holotype (457–458): median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (442–445, 450–453, 455–458); apico-ventral portion of median lobe in lateral view (446–448); male sternite VIII (449, 454). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421226/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">455–456</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
